        text: 'The debt snowball method prioritizes paying off debts from smallest balance to largest, regardless of interest rate, giving you quick psychological wins. The debt avalanche method prioritizes debts from highest interest rate to lowest, which saves the most money on interest over time. Both methods require making minimum payments on all debts while directing extra funds toward the priority debt. The avalanche method is mathematically optimal, while the snowball method is often preferred for its motivational benefits.',
